ied early in life to the Holy Roman Emperor  Henry V , and later disputed the throne of England with her cousin  Stephen . In  1128  she married  Geoffrey , Count of Anjou. A medieval chronicler commented, ‘she was a good woman, but she had little bliss with him’. The name <i>Maud</i> became quite common in England in the 19th century, when its popularity was influenced in part by  Tennyson's  poem Maud, published in  1855 , but has not been much used since the early decades of the 20th century."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Maud N was born about 1345. She had at least 1 son with Sir Robert de Betham."},"et":{"about 1345–":"umbes 1345–Surnud","1345–1379":"1345–1379","–Male":"Surnud","1367–1420":"1367–1420","1378–Male":"1378–Surnud","1345–Female":"1345–Surnud","1379":"1379","1378":"1378","1367":"1367","1345":"1345","1420":"1420","       1378":"1378","about 1345":"umbes 1345","about 1367":"umbes 1367","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Beetham, Westmorland, England":"Beetham, Westmorland, England"},"fi":{"about 1345–":"noin 1345–Kuollut","1345–1379":"1345–1379","–Male":"Kuollut","1367–1420":"1367–1420","1378–Male":"1378–Kuollut","1345–Female":"1345–Kuollut","1379":"1379","1378":"1378","1367":"1367","1345":"1345","1420":"1420","       1378":"1378","about 1345":"noin 1345","about 1367":"noin 1367","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Beetham, Westmorland, England":"Beetham, Westmorland, England"},"fr":{"about 1345–":"environ 1345–Décédée","1345–1379":"1345–1379","–Male":"Décédé","1367–1420":"1367–1420","1378–Male":"1378–Décédé","1345–Female":"1345–Décédée","1379":"1379","1378":"1378","1367":"1367","1345":"1345","1420":"1420","       1378":"1378","about 1345":"environ 1345","about 1367":"environ 1367","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Beetham, Westmorland, England":"Beetham, Westmorland, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Maud N est née environ 1345. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Sir Robert de Betham."},"de":{"about 1345–":"um 1345–Verstorben","1345–1379":"